text: 126 shares 'I need more botox!' she quipped, touching her forehead. Daily Mail Australia previously revealed how the 25-year-old was a glamour model who attended parties at the Playboy Mansion. Old photos of the hair salon manager also showed that she has been seemingly undergoing a physical transformation in recent years. Welcome home: On Tuesday night's episode of Married At First Sight, Cheryl went to Perth with new 'husband' Andrew Meet the parents: The 25-year-old met Andrew's family for the first time Pout: Throwback snaps of Cheryl show just how different she looks Metamorphosis: Snaps of Cheryl from a couple of years ago show her sporting thinner lips compared to her currently plump pout Snaps of Cheryl from a few years ago show her sporting thinner lips compared to her currently plump pout. The brunette's eyebrows are also significantly thinner in previous photos, and her nose looks slightly different. In January, Daily Mail Australia revealed that Cheryl had attended at least two parties at Hugh Hefner's infamous mansion in Los Angeles. The reality TV show contestant first visited the mansion in 2011, with her sister Sarah-Jane, when she was just 20 years old. Brows: The busty brunette's eyebrows also appear different in previous photos Playboy guest: In January, Daily Mail Australia revealed that Cheryl attended at least two parties at Hugh Hefner's infamous mansion in Los Angeles (pictured in 2014) Chummy with The Candyman: More recently, she was spotted parting at a Gold Coast bikini party run by millionaire tobacco tycoon Travers Beynon, known as 'The Candyman' (Pictured right, in 2013) The following year Cheryl, who at that time had blonde hair, returned to LA to attend another one of the Playboy parties, this time donning lingerie. After her second visit, Cheryl Tweeted Hugh Hefner's then-number one 'girlfriend' Holly Madison, who responded to her message. More recently, she was spotted partying at a Gold Coast bikini party run by millionaire tobacco tycoon Travers Beynon, known as 'The Candyman'. Share or comment on this article 126
